  "title": "Group Executive Chef",
  "description": "<p>- Location(s): CBD</p><p>- Working Days: 6 days/week</p><p>- Working Hours: 11am to 11pm (2 hrs break)</p><p></p><p>Job Description & Requirements:</p><p>- Develop and implement culinary strategies for multiple outlets to align with the company’s vision and brand identity.</p><p>- Create and standardize menus across outlets, ensuring consistency in flavor, presentation, and quality.</p><p>- Oversee the creation of seasonal, promotional, and event-specific menus to attract customers and increase revenue.</p><p>- Ensure uniformity in food preparation, portion sizes, and presentation across all locations.</p><p>- Maintain high standards of food safety, sanitation, and hygiene at all outlets.</p><p>- Monitor food costs, waste, and portion control across locations to optimize resources and reduce wastage.</p><p>- Develop and enforce standardized procedures for kitchen cleanliness, equipment maintenance, and safety protocols.</p><p></p><p>We Offer:</p><p>- Competitive salary and benefits package.</p><p>- Opportunities for career advancement and skill development.</p><p>- A dynamic and supportive work environment.</p><p>- Staff discounts on meals.</p><p></p><p>How to Apply:</p><p>Sent your resume and a cover letter via this platform</p>",
